Project: Ecommerce Application Maintenance/Investor System
Role: Lead developer

Description: Banks usually give out loans to the debtors. Whenever a loan is given default risk is associated with them. To hedge this risk the banks float Asset Backed Securities (ABS) and Mortgage Backed Securities (MBS). The originator (agency that gives loans) sells a pool of mortgage and assets to an SPV (Special Purpose Vehicle). SPV is usually a company floated by the originator. SPV then issues securities backed by those assets. SPV then categorizes the various securities based upon their risk. This logical grouping of the collaterals / securities is known as CLASS. Classes are assigned ratings such as A1, B2, AAA, BB, etc. The rating for the classes is done on the basis of the risk associated with them. The investors then buy these securities. The Trustee looks after this whole agreement starting from the debtor to the investors. Trustee is responsible so that the whole process is carried out following all the legal procedures meeting all the set deadlines. This whole process is known as a DEAL.

Responsibilities
